<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-7577] cqlsh: CTRL-R history search not working on OSX</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-7577</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;recursive-history-search&lt;/em&gt; via ctrl-R does not work in cqlsh. The history itself works via cursor up/down.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It works on Linux (and I guess on Windows with cygwin) but not on my Mac.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;OSX - plain Terminal program&lt;br/&gt;
C* 2.0.x, 2.1, trunk&lt;/p&gt;</environment>
        <key id="12728402">CASSANDRA-7577</key>
            <summary>cqlsh: CTRL-R history search not working on OSX</summary>
